postcontent: Shotgun is mostly used on short distances, that is why you can see red dot or holographic non-magnifying sight on a shotgun more often than optic sight. Typically, red dot, reflex and holographic sights are designed for fast target acquisition usually within a 100-yard range, which is suitable for both hunting and tactical situations. Many shooting experts recommend that you shoot with both eyes open especially in a tactical situation. Red dot sights allow shooters to keep both eyes open because of the dedicated focusing of the sight. The shooting eye is not strained when using the sight.

postcontent: I have a beautiful Cetme with wood furnisher. I am the second owner and the first owner (a friend of mine) never shot it. They are not easy to obtain, especially an older one like this is in the condition its in.The barrel looks like a mirror and the rifling is very strong. Finish is around 99%. This is an older version so it does not have a pictinny rail on it. It is missing the bird cage flash hider. As i stated before the previous owner never shot it so when i took it out to fire the loose barrel device flew off and i could never find it hahaha. With that said the threads look great! She just needs a muzzle device. The original brakes are pretty cheap and can be bought on clear view investments for $7. The reason for me parting ways with this amazing firearms is due to me focusing more on kalishnikov platforms instead of the G3 style. I need the safe space and this rifle (while very collectible and reliable) doesnt fit my current interests. It comes with a mag holder and 2 mags. Mags for the cetme run around $4 and this cetme will take HK mags but they are a little higher in price. Not in a hurry to sell, price is firm.
